menu "STM32"

menu "Pin Map"

# Per-peripheral pin assignments validated against ST's open-pin-data XML.
# Each `choice` only lists (pin, AF) combos ST published as valid for that
# signal on the STM32F407V package. The selected entry is rendered into
# `board::k<Name>` constants by scripts/generate_stm32_config.py. Add a new
# peripheral by adding a choice block here AND a PinmapEntry in
# generate_stm32_config.py.
#
# Layout: Peripheral family (UART, SPI, TIM, ...) -> Instance (UART2, ...) ->
# Per-signal choice. Mirrors the silicon hierarchy and keeps related signals
# colocated as more peripherals come online.

