menu "Battery Monitor"

config STM32_BATTERY_SAMPLE_PERIOD_MS
    int "Sample period (ms)"
    range 1 1000
    default 100
    help
      Period for reading the battery voltage/current ADC channels. Lower
      values update telemetry faster but spend more slow-loop time sampling
      analog inputs. The driver still filters the readings before publishing.

config STM32_BATTERY_ADC_REFERENCE_MV
    int "ADC reference voltage (mV)"
    range 1000 3600
    default 3300
    help
      VDDA/reference voltage used by ADC1 in millivolts. Set this to the
      measured 3.3 V rail if it differs from the nominal value; voltage and
      current accuracy are directly proportional to this setting.

config STM32_BATTERY_ADC_OVERSAMPLE_COUNT
    int "ADC oversample count"
    range 1 64
    default 16
    help
      Number of ADC conversion pairs averaged each battery sample period.
      Increase to reduce analog noise; decrease to reduce sampling time.

config STM32_BATTERY_FILTER_ALPHA_PERMILLE
    int "Filter alpha (permille)"
    range 1 1000
    default 250
    help
      Low-pass filter coefficient in thousandths. 1000 publishes each new
      sample directly; lower values smooth voltage/current telemetry more.

config STM32_BATTERY_ADC_TIMEOUT_US
    int "ADC conversion timeout (us)"
    range 100 10000
    default 1000
    help
      Maximum time allowed for each ADC conversion before the sample is
      discarded and the previous battery reading is retained.

menu "Voltage"

config STM32_BATTERY_VOLTAGE_MULTIPLIER_MILLI
    int "Voltage multiplier x1000"
    range 1000 100000
    default 11000
    help
      Battery-voltage multiplier in thousandths applied to the ADC pin
      voltage. For example, use 11000 when 1.000 V on PC0 represents 11.000 V
      battery voltage. Calibrate this from measured pack voltage versus ADC
      pin voltage.

config STM32_BATTERY_VOLTAGE_OFFSET_MV
    int "Voltage offset (mV)"
    range -2000 2000
    default 0
    help
      Signed correction added after voltage scaling. Use this to remove a
      small fixed offset after the divider multiplier is calibrated.

